  "text": "Another interesting finding noted in our study was a marked decrease in both systolic and diastolic blood pressure. This decrease occurred at 1 month after DJBL implantation for systolic and 3 months after DJBL implantation for diastolic blood pressure, respectively. Interestingly, blood pressure remained decreased at 3 months after DJBL removal. A possible mechanism responsible for decreased blood pressure may include the combination of weight loss and increased GLP1 levels through similar mechanisms suggested for GLP1 receptor agonists [CITATION_1] .",
